# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your own values.
#
#   cp .env.example .env        (or just copy/paste it in your editor)
#
# `.env` is gitignored and a pre-commit hook blocks these values from ever
# being committed. Never paste real values into this example file, into a
# commit, into an issue, or into a chat.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WHICH SECTION DO I FILL IN?
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#   * Polymarket US (US users, sign up with phone/email, fund with a bank card
#     -- NO crypto wallet)          -> fill in SECTION A. Leave B blank.
#   * Polymarket crypto (global, on-chain, funded with USDC on Polygon)
#                                   -> fill in SECTION B. Leave A blank.
#
# You only need one. Filling in neither is fine too -- the app still runs in
# fake-data mode with no credentials at all.


# ===========================================================================
# SECTION A -- POLYMARKET US  (api.polymarket.us)
# ===========================================================================
# Generate these at https://polymarket.us/developer
#
# !! SECURITY -- READ THIS !!
# Polymarket US does NOT offer read-only API keys. This ONE key can also PLACE
# AND CANCEL ORDERS. Anyone who gets it can trade with your money.
#
# This app is built so it CANNOT do that: the client has exactly one request in
# it (GET /v1/portfolio/positions). There is no order-placing code anywhere in
# this repo, so a bug cannot accidentally trade. But the key itself is still
# powerful -- treat it like a password:
#
#   * keep it in this .env file only (gitignored)
#   * never paste it into a chat, an issue, a screenshot, or a commit
#   * revoke it at https://polymarket.us/developer the moment you suspect a
#     leak -- and revoke it when you stop using this dashboard

# Your API Key ID -- a UUID, e.g. 3f8a1c2e-9b4d-4a17-8e0f-5c6d7e8f9a0b
POLYMARKET_US_KEY_ID=

# Your Secret Key -- a base64 string (this is an Ed25519 private key).
# This is the sensitive one. It signs your API requests.
POLYMARKET_US_SECRET_KEY=


# ===========================================================================
# SECTION B -- POLYMARKET CRYPTO  (data-api.polymarket.com)
# ===========================================================================
# The global/on-chain platform. NO key or secret is needed -- your position
# data there is fully public. All it needs is your public wallet address (the
# Polymarket proxy wallet, from your profile URL: polymarket.com/profile/0x...).
#
# A wallet address is not a cryptographic secret, but it IS a permanent public
# identifier: publishing it links your identity to your entire betting history.
# Keep it here, never in a commit.
#
# You can also just type it into the app's Wallet field instead of setting it
# here. If anything ever asks you for a PRIVATE KEY or SEED PHRASE, that is not
# this project -- do not paste it anywhere.
POLYMARKET_WALLET_ADDRESS=


# ===========================================================================
# OPTIONAL
# ===========================================================================
# Where the local SQLite database lives (your wallet + saved checkpoints).
# Defaults to data/polymarket_tracker.db, which is gitignored.
# POLYMARKET_TRACKER_DB=
